			I second the idea of using a steamer, or rigging up some kind of steamer big enough to accommodate the spuds if the steamer you already have -- IF you have one -- isn't big enough. Perhaps a cake rack in a large skillet, with simmering water under the rack (you'd have to keep it topped up, as it would be shallow and would likely simmer away to nothingness if you didn't....). Good luck!<br />
			
