			I made a wonderful change to this recipe for an early Thanksgiving dinner I went to last night. I found this wonderful set of grape seed oils that have various flavors like lemon, garlic, basil, and even chili (plus they are all sustainably made in Napa Valley with no extra additives except the plants used for the flavor). I used the chili flavored oil instead of the olive oil, and let me tell you, they were fantastic. The chili flavoring is not very hot, and it was the perfect amount to really kick these potatoes up (another) notch. If you are interested, their website is <a href="http://www.grapeseedoil.com">www.grapeseedoil.com</a>. I found them at the Green Festival last weekend, and I fell in love with the flavors right away.<br />
			
